Reflect.deleteProperty

Deprecates thedeletekeyword

Examples ofincorrectcode for this rule when used without exceptions:

/*eslint prefer-reflect: "error"*/

delete foo.bar; // deleting object property

Examples ofcorrectcode for this rule when used without exceptions:

/*eslint prefer-reflect: "error"*/

delete bar; // deleting variable
Reflect.deleteProperty(foo, 'bar');

Note: For a rule preventing deletion of variables, seeno-delete-var instead

Examples ofcorrectcode for this rule with the{ "exceptions": ["delete"] }option:

/*eslint prefer-reflect: ["error", { "exceptions": ["delete"] }]*/

delete bar
delete foo.bar
Reflect.deleteProperty(foo, 'bar');
